-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Dufry, Eurazeo, GlaxoSmithKline
-- 
-- Mon Aug 25, 2014 02:23AM EDT
-- None



Aug 25 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including Dufry, Wendel and GlaxoSmithKline, on Monday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Eurazeo SA <EURA.PA>: SocGen raises to buy from hold * GlaxoSmithKline PLC <GSK.L>: SocGen raises target price to 1920p from 1900p; rating buy  Following is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Monday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.  * Dufry AG <DUFN.VX>: Credit Suisse raises target price to Sfr 185 from Sfr 170; outperform * Eurazeo SA <EURA.PA>: SocGen raises to buy from hold * Eurazeo SA <EURA.PA>: SocGen cuts target price to 60.5 euros from 63 euros * GlaxoSmithKline PLC <GSK.L>: SocGen raises target price to 1920p from 1900p; rating buy * Tarkett <TKTT.PA>: Raymond James cuts target price to 29 euros from 31 euros; outperform